	<h2>Why Clinical Trials are Important</h2>
	<p class="reasons">- Discover cures for diseases</p>
	<div></div>
	<p class="reasons">- Discover new ways to detect and diagnose diseases</p>
	<div></div>
	<p class="reasons">- Determine side affects fo cures</p>
	<div></div>
	<p class="reasons">- Can give terminal patients more time/cure them </p>
	
	<div></div>
	
	
	
	<h3>Tay-Sachs Clinical Trials</h3> <img src="https://assets.forwardcdn.com/images/cropped/baby-with-tay-sachs-1492640071.jpg?">
	<p class="taysachs">Tay-Sachs: A rare genetic disorder that destroys nerves in the brain and spinal chord </p>
	<p class="taysachs">Ongoing Clinical Trials: <a href="https://www.umassmed.edu/gtc/our-research/tay-sachs-disease/">Gene therapy trials conducted by UMASS,</a> and <a href="http://www.curetay-sachs.org/index.jsp">IntraBio creates drug/potential cure</a></p> 
	<p class="taysachs">Click <a href="http://www.curetay-sachs.org/index.jsp">here</a> to get more information on Tay-Sachs and available research.</p>
	
	
	<div></div>	
	
	<h4>Ebola Clinical Trials</h4> <img src="http://www.nfid.org/idinfo/ebola/ebola-image.jpg">
	<p class="ebola">Ebola: A virus that causes severe bleeding, organ failure, and can lead to death </p>
	<p class="ebola">Ongoing Clinical Trials: <a href="https://clinicaltrials.gov/ct2/show/NCT00072605">Trial Vaccine/Potential Cure</a>
	<p class="ebola"> Click <a href="http://www.nfid.org/idinfo/ebola">here</a> for more information on the disease
	
